"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by Association of Convenience Stores&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nRecommendations:a)\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nInclude convenience store retailers within the scope of the English carrier bag levy to encourage charitable donations.\nb)\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nExempt small businesses with less than 250 FTE employees from having to report back information such as the proceeds of the charge to central Government. \n&#xa0;\nSupport for the levy&#xa0;\nProposed small business exemption&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n“We need to charge for plastic bags. Customers will only cut back on usage if it will cost them money\n.\n We would be delighted to give the money raised to charity\n,\n and it would not be difficult to organise\n.\n \nPlease lobby the Government\n to include small shops\n.” David \nCharman\n, Owner, \nParkfoot\n Garage Ltd.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Supporting existing retail practices&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n9 December 2013\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nAnnex 1 – Voice of Local Shops Survey 2013: Carrier Bag QuestionsThinking about the use of carrier bags by your customers, which of the following statements do you support? &#xa0;\nBase: All respondents\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nStudy TotalIndies TotalSymbols TotalSample size\n1116\n615\n501\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nI don’t currently charge for carrier bags but support a mandatory 5p charge on carrier bags \n43%\n47%\n39%\nI don’t currently charge for carrier bags and I oppose a mandatory 5p charge on carrier bags\n28%\n27%\n29%\nI currently charge customers for carrier bags and support a mandatory 5p charge \n19%\n17%\n22%\nI currently charge for carrier bags but oppose a mandatory 5p charge\n3%\n1%\n5%\nDon’t Know\n6%\n7%\n5%\n&#xa0;\nWales&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n103\nI don’t currently charge for carrier bags but support a mandatory 5p charge on carrier bags \n7%\nI don’t currently charge for carrier bags and I oppose a mandatory 5p charge on carrier bags\n3%\nI currently charge customers for carrier bags and support a mandatory 5p charge \n75%\nI currently charge for carrier bags but oppose a mandatory 5p charge\n10%\nDon’t Know\n6%\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n Please refer to the table provided in Annex 1. ACS’ Voice of Local Survey tracks 1100 retailers’ optimism for their sales every three months and also asks topical questions relevant to the period of release. The survey covers England, Wales and Scotland. \n \nhttp://www.assemblywales.org/sub-ld8664-em-e.pdf\n \n"